Bollywood superstar Amitabh Bachchan took time off on Tuesday to play some football with kids at the Mohammedan Sporting ground, where he had gone for a film shoot.Bachchan, who entered the famous ground at 7.45 a.m., spent the entire day in the club premises, shooting some scenes for his upcoming film TE3N. He was seen sitting in the gallery, the club tent and the ground.The actor, who sported a black, striped T-shirt and black trousers, with a muffler around his neck, had some fun on the ground of the iconic club, which is celebrating its 125th anniversary this year.The club felicitated Bachchan and made him an honorary life member. The club also invited the legendary actor to be the chief guest at the clubâ€™s 125th anniversary gala to be held later in the year.